The '''Otoh Gunga Zoological Research Facility''', also known as '''Otoh Gunga Municipal Zoo''' or '''Otoh Gunga Zoo''', was a [[Zoo/Legends|zoo]] and [[Laboratory/Legends|laboratory]] structure located in the [[Gungan/Legends|Gungan]] city of [[Otoh Gunga/Legends|Otoh Gunga]].

==Description==
Built inside of a [[Hydrostatic bubble/Legends|hydrostatic bubble]] linked with the other structures of the underwater city of Otoh Gunga, the Zoological Research Facility, or ZRF, was a place where wild animals could be seen and studied. Primarily featuring marine animals that inhabited the swamps and undersea trenches of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]], the zoo also kept terrestrial beasts and avian species. Each species of creature was kept in a custom habitat where a small [[Holodisplay/Legends|holodisplay]] presented information on the animal so that visitors might learn and visualize how the animal behaved in the wild.<ref name="NoP" />

Maintained by highly trained keepers, such as [[Yr'Apaly Omin]], the ZRF was a secure area, with its own security. Containing a research institute that investigated all manner of scientific inquiry, marine scientists, biologists, and researchers milled about the ZRF on a daily basis.<ref name="NoP" />

Sometime before the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]], [[Jar Jar Binks/Legends|Jar Jar Binks]] accidentally deactivated half of the bubbles containing the wildlife. Releasing several animals from the zoo into the city caused a major commotion and upset [[Boss/Legends|Boss]] [[Rugor Nass/Legends|Rugor Nass]], who sentenced Binks to six months of hard labor in the [[Quarry penal colony]].

